  "text": "Further support for a role of PKs in reproductive function can be gleaned from PKR2 knockout mice, which show hypoplasia of the reproductive tract [CITATION_1] . This phenotype has been explained by the lack of GnRH neurones in the hypothalamus of these animals. However, it is possible that the loss of a direct role of PKR2 in the reproductive tract contributes to the observed atrophy of these tissues. PK2 or PKR1 knockout mice do not show abnormalities in the reproductive tract [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
